snippet: The party led by former Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif, once a political exile, appeared to have enough seats to form a government easily.
abstract: Former Pakistani Prime Min Nawaz Sharif returns to cusp of power, taking commanding lead in parliamentary election in which voters brave Taliban intimidation to cast ballots with historic prospects for country's democracy; record turnout is reported in several cities, and even with just partial returns, Sharif's party appears to have secured enough seats to form government.

byline.contributor: Reporting was contributed by Salman Masood from Gujar Khan, Pakistan; Zia ur-Rehman from Karachi, Pakistan; Ihsanullah Tipu Mehsud from Peshawar, Pakistan; and Douglas Schorzman from New York.

lead_paragraph: The party led by former Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif, once a political exile, appeared to have enough seats to form a government easily.

headline.seo: Nawaz Sharif Set to Regain Power in Pakistan
headline.main: Ex-Premier Is Set to Regain Power in Pakistan Vote
headline.print_headline: Ex-Premier Is Set To Regain Power In Pakistan Vote
